WEBVTT

00:33.229 --> 00:34.857
Nothing says "American family"...

00:35.024 --> 00:37.902
...like raising the flag
with your wife and two kids.

00:38.069 --> 00:40.696
Let Wednesday begin.

00:43.367 --> 00:47.246
Look at that bald eagle, kids.
Majestic.

00:47.413 --> 00:50.668
"I'm dead, and I need a kiss."

00:52.086 --> 00:54.297
Cut it out. Go. Get it away.
I will kill you.

00:54.464 --> 00:56.132
Steve, Hayley, knock it off.

00:56.299 --> 00:59.804
Steve, go mail that to Donovan McNabb.
See if he'll sign it.

00:59.970 --> 01:02.516
Hey, it's our favorite gay neighbors.

01:04.810 --> 01:07.729
What are you guys doing today?
Shopping? Brunching? Parading?

01:07.896 --> 01:09.857
Or taking the day off
and just being gay?

01:10.024 --> 01:11.192
Dad, what are you doing?

01:11.360 --> 01:15.114
Just reminding Greg and Terry
I'm cool with the man-on-man crowd.

01:15.280 --> 01:18.243
You two probably wanna gossip.
Dish, you queenie bitches.

01:18.410 --> 01:20.871
Actually, we do have some big news.

01:21.038 --> 01:25.459
- We've decided to have a baby.
- Congratulations. Are you adopting?

01:25.626 --> 01:26.837
No, we're having our own.

01:27.003 --> 01:30.007
Terry thinks we can handle
this sort of seismic life change...

01:30.174 --> 01:33.386
...so here goes nothing.

01:33.553 --> 01:35.848
Take my hand.

01:36.557 --> 01:39.060
Guys, guys, a baby's not like a fire.

01:39.227 --> 01:41.896
You can't just
rub two sticks together and:

01:42.063 --> 01:43.773
We're doing in vitro fertilization.

01:43.940 --> 01:46.777
- In vitro? What's that?
- Well, we've got an egg donor.

01:46.944 --> 01:48.947
They'll combine her eggs
with our sperm...

01:49.114 --> 01:51.283
...and implant those embryos
in a surrogate...

01:51.450 --> 01:53.952
...where, God willing,
one of them will grow to term.

01:54.120 --> 01:57.666
<i>I thought I saw every episode of
Star Trek. Wait, is this Deep Space Nine?</i>

01:57.833 --> 02:00.627
I won't watch that. It's garbage.
I'll tell you why. One...

02:00.794 --> 02:02.629
Stan, this isn't science fiction.

02:02.796 --> 02:06.427
It's real fiction.
And I think it's fantastic.

02:06.594 --> 02:08.761
We're even converting our gym
into a nursery.

02:08.928 --> 02:12.183
Which is fine, because I don't need
to work out ever again.

02:13.435 --> 02:15.145
Help me.

02:17.689 --> 02:21.152
I don't believe it. I let them be gay,
and this is how they repay me?

02:21.319 --> 02:22.779
What's that supposed to mean?

02:22.946 --> 02:24.616
If two men open up to each other...

02:24.782 --> 02:28.119
...and share a love more exquisite
than anything a man and woman...

02:28.286 --> 02:30.664
...could ever find together,
that's their problem.

02:30.831 --> 02:34.169
But when they try to bring a child into it,
I gotta put my foot down.

02:34.336 --> 02:37.923
Well, excuse me, but who are you to say
whether they should have kids?

02:38.089 --> 02:39.842
A concerned American, Francine.

02:40.009 --> 02:43.680
I've always said you can't raise normal
children in an abnormal environment.

02:43.847 --> 02:46.850
You know what that'll do to society?
Girls playing with trucks.

02:47.017 --> 02:49.771
Boys playing with dolls.
Horses eating each other.

02:49.938 --> 02:51.397
Yes, horses eating each other.

02:51.564 --> 02:53.858
- Read the Bible.
- Well, I admire Greg and Terry.

02:54.025 --> 02:56.195
They're taking their lives
to the next level.

02:56.362 --> 02:58.114
Francine, it's unnatural.

02:58.281 --> 03:01.369
I mean, why don't I just start a family
with the couch?

03:01.535 --> 03:04.413
Hey, kids. How was school?
Brush your teeth. Stay off drugs.

03:04.580 --> 03:09.211
Hello, wife. Miss me? I missed you.

03:09.836 --> 03:12.047
Oh, man,
the things I'm gonna do to you.

03:12.214 --> 03:14.717
Lie on your stomach.
I'll prop you up with the kids.

03:14.884 --> 03:17.304
- Stan.
- See how weird it gets, Francine?

03:27.358 --> 03:31.028
- Three, two, one.
- Three, two, one.

03:43.460 --> 03:46.548
- We totally got you.
- We totally got you.

03:47.800 --> 03:52.889
Allow me to impress upon you
the severe mistake you have made.

03:53.056 --> 03:55.767
For years,
my conduct has been largely benign...

03:55.935 --> 04:00.231
...and yet, without provocation,
you have severed our dÃ©tente...

04:00.398 --> 04:05.864
