04:28.182 --> 04:34.355
...you will regret the day
you crossed the wrong fish.

04:35.608 --> 04:37.193
He didn't think it was funny.

04:42.283 --> 04:45.620
I found some of Steve and Hayley's
baby clothes in the basement.

04:45.787 --> 04:47.748
I'm gonna bring them
to Greg and Terry's.

04:47.915 --> 04:49.082
Good thinking, Francine.

04:49.249 --> 04:52.336
They can put them on their dog
and forget about this baby thing.

04:52.503 --> 04:54.756
All they wanna do
is dress something up.

04:54.923 --> 04:57.426
No. This is for when
they have their baby.

04:57.593 --> 05:00.430
They're doing a wonderful thing,
and I want them to know...

05:00.597 --> 05:03.433
...that I support them
in this beautiful endeavor.

05:03.600 --> 05:06.604
I couldn't agree more. Just replace
"support" with "condemn"...

05:06.771 --> 05:10.316
...and "beautiful endeavor"
with "horrible abomination."

05:14.821 --> 05:18.034
My shipment of Bavarian chocolate.

05:18.202 --> 05:20.662
Are you crazy?
What if Klaus got to it first?

05:20.828 --> 05:25.001
You heard him.
He wants to cleave us in twain.

05:26.795 --> 05:28.672
It looks like chocolate.

05:28.838 --> 05:31.300
You know what else
looks like chocolate? Poison...

05:31.467 --> 05:34.137
...when dipped in chocolate.

05:34.930 --> 05:35.973
Lovely day.

05:36.139 --> 05:38.559
- Yes, lovely.
- Yes.

05:39.434 --> 05:40.520
He's a psychopath.

05:40.687 --> 05:43.065
- Let's hide in your attic.
- And never go to sleep.

05:43.232 --> 05:47.069
- We could take turns sleeping.
- You are fantastic under pressure.

05:47.486 --> 05:48.529
Stay humble.

05:50.615 --> 05:51.993
Hi, Terry.

05:52.159 --> 05:55.997
I just wanted you guys to know
I think it's great what you're doing...

05:56.163 --> 05:57.707
...and I'm here for you two.

05:57.874 --> 06:02.338
So I brought you some of Steve
and Hayley's old baby clothes.

06:02.505 --> 06:05.550
Thanks, but at this rate,
we're not gonna be having a baby.

06:05.717 --> 06:07.803
Greg keeps shooting down
all our surrogates.

06:07.970 --> 06:10.140
- We're down to two candidates.
- Yellow teeth.

06:10.307 --> 06:13.019
- She's a smoker. She's out.
- Okay, so down to one.

06:13.185 --> 06:17.273
<i>Oh, no. Terry, look. This girl lists
her favorite movie as Erin Brockovich.</i>

06:17.440 --> 06:20.152
Is that the message
you want our baby to absorb in utero?

06:20.319 --> 06:22.654
Show your boobs
to get clean drinking water?

06:22.821 --> 06:24.990
You know what?
I'm exhausted. You exhaust me.

06:25.157 --> 06:27.201
You can't blame him
for being picky, Terry.

06:27.368 --> 06:29.872
You're putting a lot of trust
in a complete stranger.

06:30.039 --> 06:31.874
What are we gonna do?

06:32.041 --> 06:33.459
- I'll do it.
- What?

06:33.625 --> 06:35.879
- I'll carry your baby.
- Really?

06:36.046 --> 06:37.631
It makes perfect sense.

06:37.798 --> 06:39.508
I live right across the street...

06:39.675 --> 06:42.511
...and both pregnancies
were a breeze for me.

06:42.678 --> 06:46.976
Doctor says
I have a big, spongy cervix.

06:47.143 --> 06:49.479
Listen to me
bragging about my vagina.

06:49.646 --> 06:52.983
It's last week's PTA meeting
all over again.

06:58.364 --> 07:00.658
Stan, honey?

07:01.284 --> 07:02.328
Yes?

07:02.495 --> 07:05.123
Remember how I said
I wanted to help Greg and Terry?

07:05.290 --> 07:09.753
Well, a couple weeks ago,
I agreed to be their surrogate...

07:09.920 --> 07:13.007
...and now I'm pregnant
with their baby.

07:30.487 --> 07:34.408
Francine, what the hell?
You have something you wanna tell me?

07:34.575 --> 07:35.618
You need me alive.

07:35.785 --> 07:39.623
I'm the only one who remembers
where you took off your shoes.

07:42.460 --> 07:44.587
We'll tell him later.

07:48.801 --> 07:51.847
You guys have been so great,
making us dinner every night.

07:52.013 --> 07:55.350
And how good do you feel sticking
to the appropriate gay activities...

07:55.517 --> 07:57.270
...instead of that baby nonsense?

07:57.436 --> 08:00.566
And, look, you got to wear an apron.
That's almost a dress.

08:00.732 --> 08:02.776
- I'll clear.
- No, no, no. Let me.

08:02.943 --> 08:05.237
No, no. Let her.
She needs to get some exercise.

08:05.404 --> 08:08.116
Look how fat she is.
My God, you've let yourself go.

08:08.283 --> 08:12.413
You made your point, Francine.
I love you for who you are.

08:12.580 --> 08:15.792
Jeez. I'm gonna
go look at thin women online.

08:15.959 --> 08:18.462
I can't believe you haven't told him
you're pregnant.

08:18.629 --> 08:22.133
- I can't believe Stan hasn't noticed.
- I can't believe a lot of things:

08:22.300 --> 08:25.679
That there's life on Mars,
that someone's married to Larry King...

08:25.846 --> 08:29.142
...that the Harlem Globetrotters
have never lost a ga...

08:29.309 --> 08:33.647
- The baby's kicking.
- Greg, feel.

08:35.107 --> 08:37.068
Oh, God. What does it want?

08:37.235 --> 08:41.405
I can't give it what it wants.
I'm a terrible father. I'm Bing Crosby.

08:44.994 --> 08:47.331
Has this can been out of your sight
at any point?

08:47.497 --> 08:52.962
- No. Yes. No. I can't remember anymore.
- Well, how am I supposed to eat it?

08:54.005 --> 08:57.550
Just sitting here, month after month,
waiting for Klaus' revenge...

08:57.718 --> 08:58.969
...it's maddening.

08:59.136 --> 09:02.599
- I hear something.
- It's him. He's doing it.

09:02.766 --> 09:08.606
Hold on. It was just a spider.
Steve, it was just a spider.

09:11.193 --> 09:13.029
- Yeah? Yeah? Yeah?
- Yeah? Yeah? Yeah?

09:13.196 --> 09:16.157
Wait. Unless he sent the spider...

09:16.324 --> 09:20.245
...to distract us
from what he's doing behind us!

09:20.412 --> 09:23.625
- There's nothing there!
- Yeah, this time!

09:24.166 --> 09:26.419
My son hasn't been to school
in six months?

09:26.586 --> 09:29.298
I'm sure that's not right. You...
Oh, I have another call.

09:29.465 --> 09:31.385
Hold on. Or don't.
I'm not coming back.

09:31.968 --> 09:33.177
Hello?

09:33.344 --> 09:34.888
Test results?

09:35.055 --> 09:37.600
But my wife's far too fat
to be pregnant.

09:37.767 --> 09:41.271
Okay, let's play the CD
your daddies bought for you.

09:46.945 --> 09:50.282
You sleep in a stomach.

09:52.868 --> 09:56.206
Outside a stomach.

09:56.373 --> 10:00.710
Your doctor called. He said the baby
you're carrying for two gay men is fine...

10:00.877 --> 10:02.547
...and you should be very excited.

10:02.713 --> 10:05.217
Do you know how many babies
are born without an anus?

10:05.384 --> 10:07.219
That's it. No more WebMD for you.

10:07.386 --> 10:08.847
You impregnated my wife.

10:09.013 --> 10:11.266
And now I'm gonna kick
your tight little asses.

10:11.432 --> 10:13.685
Oh, you want some? Rumble, Terry.

10:29.204 --> 10:32.040
