and raising it in there is super-wrong.

10:53.568 --> 10:56.779
Well, it's happening
whether you like it or not.

10:56.946 --> 10:59.032
Francine!

10:59.658 --> 11:01.118
- Did we miss the rumble?
- Yes.

11:01.285 --> 11:04.288
Oh, you had to go back
and change your belt.

11:05.539 --> 11:09.462
Francine, you are single-handedly
bringing on the downfall of society.

11:09.629 --> 11:12.591
It's my body, it's my decision.

11:12.758 --> 11:16.553
You accused Greg and Terry of creating
a bad environment for this child.

11:16.720 --> 11:18.556
You're the one
who's stressing Mom out.

11:18.723 --> 11:20.475
- That's not good for the baby.
- But...

11:20.642 --> 11:23.603
Do you wanna be responsible
for hurting an unborn life? Do you?

11:23.770 --> 11:25.898
- No.
- Stop thinking of yourself...

11:26.065 --> 11:28.818
...and start thinking about
what's best for the baby.

11:34.951 --> 11:38.163
Honey, I'm sorry.
Whether I like it or not, you're pregnant.

11:38.330 --> 11:41.041
And I have to start thinking about
the baby's well-being.

11:41.208 --> 11:43.628
So from now on,
we're in this together.

11:43.795 --> 11:48.385
- Stan, I'm using the bathroom.
- Then I too will use the bathroom.

11:48.551 --> 11:51.261
Oh, Stan.

12:08.574 --> 12:10.160
Okay, camera's rolling.

12:10.327 --> 12:12.622
And here we have
our two big manly men...

12:12.789 --> 12:14.332
...building the baby's crib.

12:14.499 --> 12:17.460
<i>I feel like I'm Tim Allen.</i>

12:18.545 --> 12:21.298
<i>- Guys, my water broke.
- What?</i>

12:23.510 --> 12:26.346
<i>- Okay, here we go.
- Oh, no. No, no. I'm not ready.</i>

12:26.513 --> 12:28.349
<i>No, no, no.</i>

12:28.516 --> 12:31.311
<i>No, no, no.</i>

12:31.478 --> 12:34.857
<i>- Greg, get in the car.
- No, no, no.</i>

12:35.023 --> 12:36.817
<i>Greg.</i>

12:36.984 --> 12:39.237
<i>- Greg.
- No!</i>

12:39.404 --> 12:40.739
<i>Remember when you thought...</i>

12:40.906 --> 12:43.617
<i>... you couldn 't wade through the foam
