12:53.546 --> 12:55.632
- So tell me, how's he been?
- How's who been?

12:55.799 --> 12:57.217
You're working with the fish.

12:57.384 --> 12:59.554
Me? How do I know
you're not working with him?

12:59.721 --> 13:01.764
I'll tell you how.

13:09.357 --> 13:11.568
- Look at us.
- We've gone crazy.

13:11.735 --> 13:14.655
- We can't live like this anymore.
- We have to confront Klaus.

13:14.822 --> 13:17.409
Yes. We must confront him.

13:17.576 --> 13:22.331
Is this an accurate mirror?
Look how long my arms are. Disgusting.

13:22.498 --> 13:25.460
Face saves it, though.
Face is glorious.

13:25.627 --> 13:29.048
Steve, I want you to lean over
and kiss my chest.

13:30.049 --> 13:31.508
Stay in the mirror.

13:35.514 --> 13:36.557
It's a girl.

13:36.724 --> 13:39.393
- It's a girl.
- It's a girl.

13:41.021 --> 13:44.984
- She's beautiful. Oh, Greg, here.
- No, no, no.

13:45.151 --> 13:47.570
I am in love with this baby.

13:47.737 --> 13:50.574
Stan, look at my precious little gift
from heaven.

13:50.741 --> 13:52.451
Oh, Terry, thank you.

13:52.618 --> 13:57.165
Stop. You were great. We all were:
You, me, Francine, Stan.

13:57.332 --> 13:59.042
Stan? Where's Stan?

14:01.671 --> 14:04.841
Don't you worry, little girl.
We're gonna find you a real home.

14:10.890 --> 14:12.810
<i>And now the Channel 3 Noon Report...</i>

14:12.977 --> 14:15.479
<i>... with anchor partners Greg Corbin
and Terry Bates.</i>

14:15.646 --> 14:19.359
A baby was reported missing today
from Langley Memorial Hospital.

14:19.526 --> 14:21.696
- The incident occurred at...
- He took our baby!

14:21.862 --> 14:24.323
- He just took her!
- Get a picture of her on-screen.

14:24.490 --> 14:26.575
- I don't have a picture.
- Then describe her.

14:26.743 --> 14:28.787
- She looks like an angel.
- What am I doing?

14:28.954 --> 14:31.582
I was a reporter, for God's sakes.
I'll track her down.

14:31.749 --> 14:34.460
- You were a food critic.
- You don't think I can find her?

14:34.627 --> 14:37.756
<i>I found a decent beignet at the airport,
I can find a baby.</i>

14:37.965 --> 14:40.802
I can't believe
your father would do something like this.

14:40.969 --> 14:42.929
- I can.
- Yeah, I guess I can too.

14:43.096 --> 14:45.224
I don't know why I said that.

14:45.391 --> 14:46.976
- Hello?
- Francine, it's me.

14:47.143 --> 14:49.354
- Stan, where are you?
- I'm here with Liberty.

14:49.521 --> 14:50.938
- Who?
- Liberty Belle.

14:51.106 --> 14:53.066
It's the name I gave
the baby I'm saving.

14:53.233 --> 14:56.946
Poor girl, I think she's slow.
She's just staring at her cheeseburger.

14:57.113 --> 14:59.866
- Stan, you bring her back right now.
- Sorry, Francine.

15:00.033 --> 15:03.663
I've prayed on this. I'm taking her
to Nebraska to put her up for adoption.

15:03.830 --> 15:06.500
What? You can't give
someone else's baby away.

15:06.667 --> 15:10.504
Nebraska begs to differ.
Gay couples have no legal rights there.

15:10.671 --> 15:12.173
Once I cross that state line...

15:12.339 --> 15:14.718
...Greg and Terry
can kiss their custody goodbye.

15:14.885 --> 15:16.971
You're never gonna
get away with this, Stan.

15:17.138 --> 15:19.849
You know I'm gonna tell them.
Why would you even call me?

15:20.016 --> 15:22.770
Something hard and black
fell off the baby's bellybutton.

15:22.936 --> 15:24.939
I thought it was beef jerky, and...

15:25.106 --> 15:27.734
Am I gonna die,
or am I stronger than ever?

15:31.155 --> 15:33.616
Okay, you win. Just do it already.

15:33.784 --> 15:35.702
- Do what?
- Get your revenge.

15:35.869 --> 15:40.166
- The water slide? The practical joke?
- Oh, yes. I had forgotten.

15:40.333 --> 15:42.668
Good. Good. Good. Us too.

15:42.835 --> 15:45.463
But now that you have reminded me...

15:45.630 --> 15:50.804
...the humiliation I suffered that day
will not go unpunished.

15:50.970 --> 15:54.182
My pain is the bubbling caldron
of molten steel...

15:54.349 --> 15:57.144
...that will forge the saber
of your demise.

15:57.311 --> 16:04.110
I shall not be denied my vengeance!

16:08.158 --> 16:10.787
Don't know why we didn't think of that
nine months ago.

16:12.080 --> 16:15.875
Thirty dollars on 2, and a cup of coffee
for the baby. She keeps dozing off.

16:16.042 --> 16:19.756
It's been 19 hours. We're still looking
for the man who kidnapped our baby.

16:19.923 --> 16:23.093
If any of our brethren in
the Rainbow Truckers Brigade spot him...

16:23.260 --> 16:24.511
...please try to stop him.

16:24.678 --> 16:28.182
They were recently seen
at the Stuckey's off Interstate 280.

16:28.349 --> 16:30.935
Liberty, they're onto us.
When will I learn?

16:31.102 --> 16:34.857
Every time I let a man take a picture
of me in a bathroom, it goes bad.

16:38.737 --> 16:40.405
We're nearly to Nebraska, Liberty.

16:40.572 --> 16:42.741
Fifty miles
to the freedom of an orphanage...

16:42.908 --> 16:44.953
...where we'll get you
some real parents.

16:45.120 --> 16:46.998
Hey, look, the heartland's on our side.

17:04.685 --> 17:06.936
The Rainbow Truckers.

17:23.415 --> 17:25.460
- Get on.
- Who are you?

17:25.626 --> 17:26.753
A friend.

17:27.296 --> 17:28.881
Hold on.

17:29.048 --> 17:31.551
Or my waist.

17:35.848 --> 17:37.516
I can't thank you enough, Lily.

17:37.683 --> 17:41.104
Well, when Al and I heard about you
on TV, we knew we had to help.

17:41.271 --> 17:42.815
Jason, this is Stan and Liberty.

17:42.981 --> 17:45.359
- They're gonna stay for dinner.
- Nice to meet you.

17:45.526 --> 17:47.863
Well, that's a good, strong handshake,
young man.

17:48.030 --> 17:49.990
<i>You remind me
of the kid from Old Yeller.</i>

17:50.157 --> 17:52.493
- Let's go shoot your dog.
- I don't have a dog.

17:52.659 --> 17:54.746
We'll get you one,
and then we'll shoot it.

17:56.498 --> 17:58.417
Stan, this is my daughter, Mary.

17:58.584 --> 18:03.047
Oh, a baby. I love babies.
Jesus was a baby.

18:03.215 --> 18:06.677
Yes, he was.
And he was also a murder victim.

18:06.844 --> 18:11.224
Oh, Al's home.
Kids, go wash up for dinner.

18:11.432 --> 18:14.937
Lily, you have fantastic children,
a beautiful home.

18:15.104 --> 18:18.149
I can't wait to meet your husband
and shake his hand.

18:18.651 --> 18:20.527
Hi, honey.

18:20.693 --> 18:21.862
I see you found him.

18:22.029 --> 18:24.323
Sir, I must tell you,
you have a lovely family.

18:24.491 --> 18:25.867
You're a lucky man.

18:26.034 --> 18:28.787
Actually, "Al" is short for "Alison."
I'm a woman.

18:28.954 --> 18:30.998
Right. You know,
I love long hair on a man.

18:31.165 --> 18:34.378
Grown-up Jesus had long hair,
but his breasts weren't as luscious...

18:34.545 --> 18:37.215
- Holy shit, you're a woman!
- Yes. Lily's my partner.

18:37.381 --> 18:40.426
- We're a lesbian couple.
- Oh, my God. Does Al know?

18:40.593 --> 18:44.098
Stan, we thought if we showed you
how happy and healthy our family is...

18:44.265 --> 18:48.310
...you'd see that there's nothing wrong
with a gay couple raising children.

18:49.104 --> 18:51.481
I don't know what to say.
I was wrong.

18:51.648 --> 18:55.320
You've really opened my eyes. I'm just
gonna go change Liberty real quick...

18:55.487 --> 18:58.782
...and then we'll all sit down
to a beautiful meal.

18:59.449 --> 19:04.622
See, honey? We enlightened a bigot.
We just made the world a little better.

19:04.789 --> 19:06.791
We could have turned him in
to the cops...

19:06.958 --> 19:09.420
...but that would've just created
another monster.

19:09.587 --> 19:13.593
- Instead, we changed a mind.
- We changed a heart.

19:13.758 --> 19:17.847
This is why we left Reseda.
This, right here.

19:20.017 --> 19:21.727
Let me see if I got this right.

19:21.894 --> 19:25.398
You kidnapped us from a loving home
and are taking us to an orphanage?

19:25.565 --> 19:27.108
Yes. Your nightmare is over.

19:27.275 --> 19:30.738
It might take years, but maybe someday
a straight family will adopt you.

19:30.904 --> 19:35.035
But we already have a family,
and you said we're a great family.

19:35.201 --> 19:37.705
You seemed like a great family,
but you can't be.

19:37.872 --> 19:39.540
There's two mothers and no father.

19:39.707 --> 19:41.959
Jason, who's gonna teach you
to play football?

19:42.126 --> 19:44.921
- My football coach.
- Well, okay, that could work.

19:45.088 --> 19:48.843
Mary, who's gonna carry you on their
shoulders so you can see the parade?

19:49.010 --> 19:51.721
My mom. She's 6 feet in heels.

19:52.890 --> 19:57.187
- Move your stupid doll. It's in my space.
- She's not stupid, you're stupid.

19:57.354 --> 19:59.522
- She's my doll. Give her back.
- Give me that.

19:59.689 --> 20:04.988
Steve, Hayley, knock it off. I mean...
Wait. You fight just like my kids.

20:05.155 --> 20:09.743
- Just like normal kids.
- We are normal kids, you moron.

20:13.831 --> 20:17.461
And none of the horses
are eating each other.

20:26.097 --> 20:28.933
Oh, no. Why'd he stop?

20:31.269 --> 20:32.772
- Mom.
- Mommies.

20:32.939 --> 20:35.357
- Our angel.
- I'm sorry, guys.

20:35.525 --> 20:40.614
I was wrong. Raising kids doesn't take
straight parents, it takes loving parents.

20:40.781 --> 20:44.285
So I'm gonna take a chance
and let you guys raise your own child.

20:44.451 --> 20:47.998
Come on, give me a hug.
You know you want to.

20:49.250 --> 20:51.461
That wasn't campy at all.

20:54.673 --> 20:56.508
Oh, she is so cute.

20:56.675 --> 20:59.804
- Don't forget, you're gonna babysit.
- We don't need a babysitter.

20:59.972 --> 21:03.100
With her at home,
why would we ever wanna leave?

21:04.101 --> 21:06.896
- Did she smile when I said that?
- No.

21:07.063 --> 21:09.066
You ever gonna drop
the restraining order?

21:09.233 --> 21:10.317
No.

21:10.484 --> 21:12.862
She likes sugar in her coffee.

21:48.487 --> 21:50.574
[ENGLISH]
